        "text": "Wikis.  They sorta-blended into what we now feel as simply \"internet\" (or if you get technical they're just \"hypertext\") yet they were invented\/discovered at some point, and curiously the invention is largely social but was enabled by technical affordances (most notably, history + easy revert) and produced a media that has a distinct feel to it.\n\nP.S. Wiki walks are addictive too, but i'd say better than infinite scrolling(?)",
